BROADSWORD

MEDIUM PVE/PVP DESTROYER

DESIGNER: TobiwanKenobi

TALENTS AND BUFFS

If you spawned your Broadsword without the proper buffs, it will not operate. When you sit in the gunner seat, a message will appear stating: "Control Unit link capacity exceeded." To fix this and make the vehicle operable, you will need the following buffs applied to the ship either by yourself or another player.

Level 5 - Gunner M Module Capacity Handling
Level 4 - Cannon M Capacity Handling

You will also want decent levels for cannon M technician buffs and operating talents, as well as buffs and talents related to the other elements on the ship:

Level 3+ - All Cannon M operations talents and handling buffs
Level 3+ - Space engine thrust and fuel efficiency
Level 3+ - Retro engine and adjustor thrust

LOADOUT

The amount of fuel and ammo you will be able to carry will be dependent on the container/fuel optimization buffs you apply to the ship on spawn. If you have no container/fuel buffs, the ship will inherit the max buffs that are already associated with the BP. If you exceed a total ship mass of 400t, you will not be able to enter a medium mission portal. I recommend the following, but you can increase your load until you hit 400t:

at least 2000 rounds of Cannon Thermic Ammo M
at least 8000L of Kergon Fuel (30 mins of fuel)
at least 100 tier 3+ scrap

OPERATION

The Broadsword comes with FOX hud installed.

Press ESC to exit this text.
